        <p>
          The <b>U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA)</b> is an independent agency of the federal government. The SBA offers aid, advice, assistance and protects the interests of small businesses. There are many different SBA offices spread out throughout the country which enable small businesses a chance to interact locally with the SBA.  
